Government Relations, Project Support AnalystLocation: United Arab Emirates-Dubai-DubaiOrganization: Visa Inc.Job: Admin. SupportJob Number : #DescriptionCommon Purpose, Uncommon Opportunity.
Everyone at Visa works with one goal in mind – making sure that Visa is the best way to pay and be paid, for everyone everywhere. This is our global vision and the common purpose that unites the entire Visa team.
As a global payments technology company, tech is at the heart of what we do: Our VisaNet network processes over 13,000 transactions per second for people and businesses around the world, enabling them to use digital currency instead of cash and checks. We are also global advocates for financial inclusion, working with partners around the world to help those who lack access to financial services join the global economy. Visa’s sponsorships, including the Olympics and FIFA™ World Cup, celebrate teamwork, diversity, and excellence throughout the world. If you have a passion to make a difference in the lives of people around the world, Visa offers an uncommon opportunity to build a strong, thriving career. Visa is fueled by our team of talented employees who continuously raise the bar on delivering the convenience and security of digital currency to people all over the world. Join our team and find out how Visa is everywhere you want to be.POSITION SUMMARYTo seamlessly plan and execute critical government relations activities on behalf of the CEMEA Government Relations function, including the global Public Policy and Partnerships group.JOB SCOPEA) Plan, implement and manage all logistics associated with all scheduled and ad-hoc events for a wide range of government engagement and education programs.Key Performance Indicators include:- Write and send Invitation Letters to appropriate contacts provided by GR representative or Country Management staff.- Process program registration and monitor attendance levels proactively- Respond to all queries in a timely manner- Arrange training facilities in a timely manner based on an annual schedule manage all other details related to GR related workshops (i.e. facilitator prep and travel, production and shipping of materials, budget tracking, billing, etc.)- Provide registration details to facilitator and the GR representative involved proactively- Maintain a tracking sheet with latest registration numbers and working budget following receipt of trainers’ expense reports and invoices from vendors- Ensure all materials are reformatted and reviewed as part of the SEC Review process and the current Look, Tone & Feel (LTF) being used for government engagement and education programs- Ensure that all compliance-related requirements are met including (purchasing guidelines, T&E; and budgets).B) Ensure the CEMEA Government Relations function meets relevant compliance-related obligations.Key Performance Indicators include:- Prepare new vendor contracts, sponsorship agreements, and partnership documents in collaboration with Legal, Compliance, and Sourcing to ensure that these adhere to all relevant corporate policies- Review current vendor contracts on a regular basis to ensure that these are updated to reflect changes in the company’s relevant policies- Monitor the function’s Purchasing and T&E activities to ensure compliance with the appropriate policies to minimize “after-the-fact” situations- Manage receipt and proper records management of required reports from engaged consultants and lobbyists in line with the company’s relevant policies and procedures.C) Develop and maintain efficient knowledge management platforms for use by the entire Global Government Relations team.Key Performance Indicators include:- Ongoing development of the function’s Sharepoint site including regular maintenance of the site itself and coordination of relevant team training- Maintenance of the team’s activity calendar and regular updating of Executive Management on suchConsolidation, editing, and formatting of monthly reports for review by the Head of Government Relations, CEMEA- Manage production of Thoughts and Trends, Visa’s quarterly, externally-facing Government Relations newsletter in collaboration with Corporate Relations and external vendors- Identify appropriate opportunities to highlight the function’s work to broader internal audiences.D) Plan, implement and manage all logistics associated with regular and ad-hoc external activities and events hosted or sponsored by the Global Government Relations group.Qualifications- At least 5 years of professional experience- Excellent organizational skills and mindset- Project management/planning experience- Strong interpersonal skills- Good command of English- Intensely collaborative- Ability to work across multiple time zones- Execution-focused- Quality-oriented- Highly ethical- Innovative- Familiarity with Microsoft office including Sharepoint- Familiarity with Ariba and Oracle systems a plus- Proven knowledge of key result areas and Visa policies and processes is an advantage
